The situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan and terrorism have been condemned in all its forms by both sides and have called for a UN conference to be convened.
They called for the conclusion of the Doha Trade Round, although both sides played a role in its failure.
The EU has confirmed that it will continue to be part of the energy and climate programme, meaning that it would like to reduce emissions of harmful substances by at least 20% by 2020.
India also agrees on this, as well as that a global agreement should be signed at the next year's climate conference and that greenhouse gas emissions should be reduced by 50% by 2050.
They also want to curb the rise in food prices and have supported the convening of an international meeting to examine the financial crisis.
